result.formatted_address: 15 Queen's Road Central, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: The Landmark, Mandarin Oriental

reviews.text: I have stayed at this hotel with family twice now . Ir is by far the best hotel  we have stated in ever. The service is top notch . They  think  of everything to make your stay more comfortable . From fruit bowl and fresh pastries  face masks, foot spray all sorts of little touches which we appreciate. The spa is one of the best in any hotel. We had massages and facials all top quality . We will continue to be repeat clients in this hotel.

We stayed in this establishment 4 months ago with family. The hotel is expensive, but to compare the hotels we have stayed since (8+) The Landmark is still the best hotel we have been in. The service from walking in the front door is spot on. Its not just service with a smile, it's the genuine nature of all the staff who assisted us proactively.    Waylon and staff service A++ (any parent would be proud with an A+ :P) you guys/gals are unreal. not sure if its the training you were given, or just the experiences you have developed over years. I couldn't fault it. Rooms and Food is massive tick. Location of the hotel is perfect. shop,food,party,transport all within 100m walking distance. Hope to see the same crew when I return one day.

K & N

A sumptuous 5 star hotel. We just had lunch here and the cuisine was impressive. We cannot comment on the rooms as we didn't stay here. The food was exquisite and delicious. The price we finally paid was bewildering.

5 stars hotel indeed! the staffs here are super friendly and supreme service! the room is nice. the location is perfect for all kind of tourists or business men. 24hrs in-room dining and service. i would say it’s one of the best hotel that i have stayed. i would love to stay here again. kudos to all staffs here.
Upscale swanky hotel connected to a large mall. Neila went above and beyond in helping me get to know the area and provided some super helpful tips.
